Φ(Coaptation Cooptation) = σ(fit|absorption) ∘ ρ(articulation|erasure) ∘ λ(coordination|assimilation) ∘ β(boundary_integrity|identity_loss) ∘ δγ(movement|capture) ∘ μ(edges|engulfment) + ε | :dynamic_fit

## Operator Breakdown

- **σ (Air/Aerunik — Distinction)**: fit|absorption — Coaptation fits distinct parts together while retaining separate identities. Cooptation absorbs and appropriates, losing original intent.
- **ρ (Water/Sentaria — Relation)**: articulation|erasure — Coaptation preserves relational edges; cooptation dissolves them into the absorbing entity.
- **λ (Fire/Jvalion — Transformation)**: coordination|assimilation — Dynamic fit enables movement and interaction without forced unity.
- **β (Wood/Arboriel — Growth)**: boundary_integrity|identity_loss — Growth through maintained distinctiveness rather than through merger.
- **δγ (Earth/Humavita — Cycling)**: movement|capture — Cycling between dynamic interaction (coaptation) and absorptive capture (cooptation).
- **μ (Metal/Ferrosid — Structure)**: edges|engulfment — Valuing edges as sites of contact rather than barriers to overcome.

## Z-State
:dynamic_fit — Relational coordination where distinct parts articulate together without losing separate identities.

